OL,7,FWhile accepting that the "murderer is
OL,8,Fmentally unwell", Mrs Webber said the
OL,9,F"pre-meditated" nature and "brutality"
OL,10,Fof the attacks indicated that they
OL,11,Fwere the actions of "an individual who
OL,12,Fknew exactly what he was doing".
OL,14,FThe attorney general's considerations
OL,15,Fare unlikely to look at whether the
OL,16,Fcorrect charge was pursued in
OL,17,FCalocane's case, it is understood.
OL,19,FAny person or institution can ask for
OL,20,Fa sentence to be reviewed if they have
OL,21,Freason to think it is unduly lenient.
